#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:10
msgid "Meson"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:12
msgid ""
"Much like Autotools and CMake, Meson is a build system.  But it is meant to "
"be both fast and as user friendly as possible.  GNOME's goal is to port "
"modules to use the Meson build system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:18
msgid "Phases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:20
msgid ""
"The ``MesonBuilder`` and ``MesonPackage`` base classes come with the "
"following phases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:22
msgid "``meson`` - generate ninja files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:23
msgid "``build`` - build the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:24
msgid "``install`` - install the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:26
msgid "By default, these phases run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:28
msgid ""
"$ mkdir spack-build\n"
"$ cd spack-build\n"
"$ meson .. --prefix=/path/to/installation/prefix\n"
"$ ninja\n"
"$ ninja test  # optional\n"
"$ ninja install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:38
msgid ""
"Any of these phases can be overridden in your package as necessary. There is "
"also a ``check`` method that looks for a ``test`` target in the build file. "
"If a ``test`` target exists and the user runs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:42
msgid "$ spack install --test=root <meson-package>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:47
msgid "Spack will run ``ninja test`` after the build phase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:51
msgid "Important files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:53
msgid ""
"Packages that use the Meson build system can be identified by the presence "
"of a ``meson.build`` file. This file declares things like build instructions "
"and dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:57
msgid ""
"One thing to look for is the ``meson_version`` key that gets passed to the "
"``project`` function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:60
msgid ""
"project('gtk+', 'c',\n"
"     version: '3.94.0',\n"
"     default_options: [\n"
"       'buildtype=debugoptimized',\n"
"       'warning_level=1',\n"
"       # We only need c99, but glib needs GNU-specific features\n"
"       # https://github.com/mesonbuild/meson/issues/2289\n"
"       'c_std=gnu99',\n"
"     ],\n"
"     meson_version: '>= 0.43.0',\n"
"     license: 'LGPLv2.1+')"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:76
msgid ""
"This means that Meson 0.43.0 is the earliest release that will work. You "
"should specify this in a ``depends_on`` statement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:81
msgid "Build system dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:83
msgid ""
"At the bare minimum, packages that use the Meson build system need ``meson`` "
"and ```ninja``` dependencies. Since this is always the case, the "
"``MesonPackage`` base class already contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:87
msgid ""
"depends_on(\"meson\", type=\"build\")\n"
"depends_on(\"ninja\", type=\"build\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:93
msgid ""
"If you need to specify a particular version requirement, you can override "
"this in your package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:96
msgid ""
"depends_on(\"meson@0.43.0:\", type=\"build\")\n"
"depends_on(\"ninja\", type=\"build\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:104
msgid "Finding meson flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:106
msgid ""
"To get a list of valid flags that can be passed to ``meson``, run the "
"following command in the directory that contains ``meson.build``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:109
msgid "$ meson setup --help"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:116
msgid "Passing arguments to meson"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:118
msgid ""
"If you need to pass any arguments to the ``meson`` call, you can override "
"the ``meson_args`` method like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:121
msgid ""
"def meson_args(self):\n"
"    return [\"--warnlevel=3\"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:127
msgid "This method can be used to pass flags as well as variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:129
msgid ""
"Note that the ``MesonPackage`` base class already defines variants for "
"``buildtype``, ``default_library`` and ``strip``, which are mapped to "
"default Meson arguments, meaning that you don't have to specify these."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:135
msgid "External documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/mesonpackage.rst:137
msgid ""
"For more information on the Meson build system, see: https://mesonbuild.com/"
"index.html"
msgstr ""
